## 5.5 Time Complexity

Suppose

```
N = m × n
```

At every cell,

DFS explores nearly

```
3 choices
```

because one direction is the parent.

Hence,

```
Time Complexity

O(3^(m×n))
```

A looser upper bound is

```
O(4^(m×n))
```

---

### Why Exponential?

Because we generate

**every simple path**

between source and destination.

This problem is NP-Hard.

No polynomial solution exists for the general case.

---

## 5.6 Space Complexity

Recursion depth

```
O(m×n)
```

No extra visited array.

Matrix itself stores visited information temporarily.

Overall

```
Space Complexity

O(m×n)
```

