# 9. Why This Works

The algorithm works because:

* Every possible simple path is explored.
* No cell is visited twice in the same path.
* Every valid path reaching the destination is considered.
* Among all valid paths, the maximum length is stored.
* Backtracking restores the matrix so other paths are not affected.

Since **all possible simple paths** are examined, the maximum path found is guaranteed to be the correct answer.

